}

FoodStallChair: {
	DisplayName: Food Stall Chair
	Tooltip: I AM THE CHAIR THAT IS APPROACHING!
}

Arbiter: {
	DisplayName: Arbiter
	Tooltip:
		'''
		Hold left click to charge and raise the axe of judgment
		Release to cleave downward, sending a ground-hugging flame shockwave bursting out to both sides
		Longer charges increase the flames' reach and power
		"Judgment descends through fire"
		'''
}

Cloudwalking: {
	DisplayName: Cloudwalking
	Tooltip:
		'''
		Hold left click to charge and raise the great axe
		Release to send the axe flying forward, trailing clouds in its wake
		The axe automatically returns to you
		'''
}

AnnihilatingUniverse: {
	DisplayName: Annihilating Universe
	Tooltip:
		'''
		Wooden Arrows turn into a spread of Cosmic Bolts. 
		Hitting an enemy causes Galaxy Rifts to attack other foes and leaves behind a star close to death, eventually imploding.
		Right click to summon Projections of the Devourer that grow stronger and bigger over time. 
		Letting go of right click fires the portal used to home in on enemies before eventually dying out.
		[c/9C27B0:The End is Nigh.]
		'''
}

HeavenfallLongbow: {
	DisplayName: Heavenfall Longbow
	Tooltip:
		'''
		Fires out Pure Primordial Rainbow Light to completely annihiliate your foes in brilliance.
		Right click will have the Primordial light rain down on your foes, exploding in pure magnifience.
		Press [KEY] to start the Vientiane Trial when at max power.
		[legend]
		'''
	Legend:
		'''

		The flames of war from a billion years ago have never truly been extinguished. 
		Like smoldering embers, they traverse the endless corridors of time, burning brightly even now.
		They are the remnants of the Twilight of the Gods, the afterglow of the universe’s ancient schism, the ceaseless echoes of existence and annihilation.

		The Radiant God, embodiment of galactic order, fell in the greatest rebellion the cosmos has ever witnessed.
		The divine body shattered like a collapsing star, scattering countless brilliant fragments across every corner of the galaxy.
		Those fragments became the seeds of life, the spark of knowledge, the cradle of miracles—and yet, 
		they also bore the stain of greed, destruction, and desecration.
		Mortals revere these remnants, calling them sacred relics; 
		yet the so-called miracles crafted from them are but crude imitations of the divine, the reckless hubris of those who do not know reverence.

		But among the forgotten ruins and the echoes of legend, there exists an artifact that transcends all relics. 
		It is no mere witness to the fall of the Supreme God; it was the very weapon that cast Him into eternal oblivion—a bow of legend.
		Once wreathed in the fury of heaven’s fire, 
		it loosed the fatal arrow that sundered the divine authority and extinguished the hubris of gods, bringing their ambitions to ruin.
		As the war ended, the bow too was claimed by the tides of time, buried in the endless shroud of mystery and myth.

		Yet now, the wheel of fate turns once more. 
		The fires of heaven reignite, and that god-slaying bow shall emerge anew amid the symphony of stars.
		Once more, it shall carve the annals of history in blood and stardust.

		'''
}

